
[1]asperse

   ASPERSE, v.t. aspers'. [L. aspergo, aspersus, of ad and spargo, to
   scatter.]

   1. To bespatter with foul reports or false and injurious charges; to
   tarnish in point of reputation, or good name; to slander or calumniate;
   as, to asperse a poet of his writings; to asperse a character.

   2. To cast upon.
